							<a name="top"></a>
							<h1 class="firstletter">
								<span id="PROGRAM_HEADER_ID">Diploma In Public Relations (Intensive)</span>
							</h1>
							
							<!-- ASP DB:: INSERT PROGRAM BLURB HERE -START -->
							<p>
								<font color="Green"><b>Diploma Program - 240 course hours - Intensive Daytime</b></font><p>The Diploma in Public Relations is for students interested in acquiring the skills required to become an effective public relations practitioner. The diploma will cover oral and written communication skills within a variety of media while also teaching students the technical skills needed to use the most common software tools in the public relations industry. The diploma will also introduce students to the fundamental business practices and principles of public relations.</p><p>This program includes 40 hours of classroom time per week, scheduled Monday through Friday, between 9:00 and 18:00 each day. Students should be prepared to invest a minimum of 30 hours per week for class time, study and assignments. A schedule will be provided upon registration.</P><Table><tr><td><font color="Red">IMPORTANT</font></td></tr><tr><td><ul><li>Students can expect to spendapproximately $300 on textbooks and supplies.</li><li>All course exemptions must be requested in writing at the time of registration in order to receive a pro-rated tuition adjustment.</li><li>Any exemptions granted after the registration period will not result in a tuition reduction.</li></ul></td></tr></table><Table border="6" cellspacing="6" cellpadding="6"><caption><font color="Blue"><b>PROGRAM SCHEDULE 2011-2012</b></font></caption><tr><td><font color="blue">Session</font></td><td><font color="blue">Program Code</font></td><td><font color="blue">Tuition</font></td><td><font color="blue">Start Date</font></td><td><font color="blue">End Date</font></td></tr><tr><td>Fall</td><td>CEPR 990/AA0</td><td>$3,340</td><td>19-Sep-2011</td><td>25-Nov-2011</td></tr></tr><tr><td>Spring</td><td>CEPR 990/CC0</td><td>$3,340</td><td>26-Mar-2012</td><td>01-Jun-2012</td></tr></tr></table><br><hr><Table style= "background-color: lightblue"><tr><td><font color="Blue"><b>Did you know?</font></b></td></tr><tr><td><font color="Blue">This diploma program can also be completed in a Part-time format</td></tr><tr><td><ul><li>Diploma in Public Relations - <a href="http://siena.concordia.ca/conted/departments/program.aspx?program_id=PR&DeptName=Communications%20And%20Visual%20Arts&DeptCode=CAPHSKVA">view details</a></li></ul></td></tr></table><hr><br><font color="Maroon"><b>To qualify for the intensive daytime Diploma in Public Relations students must successfully complete the following courses:</b></font>
							</p>
							
